I placed my order for a takeout lunch box, opting for tacos over the torta. What followed was nothing short of a culinary masterpiece. The lunch box was a trove of tantalizing flavors. The tacos were generously filled with their signature carnitas - a loving testament to the art of slow-cooked, melt-in-your-mouth pork. The carnitas were impeccably seasoned, their inherent richness perfectly balanced by the tangy green salsa and a lively pico de gallo. What surprised me was the thoughtful inclusion of jalapenos and limes in the package. The jalapenos added a delightful kick of heat when desired, while the limes were perfect for squeezing over the tacos, lending a refreshing acidity that cut through the richness of the carnitas. Wrapped in soft, pliable corn tortillas, every bite was an exciting play of textures and flavors that kept my taste buds eagerly awaiting the next mouthful. Equally impressive were the sides. The Habanero Salsa delivered a more robust heat for those who crave a bit more spice, while the Guacamole provided a creamy, cooling contrast, a perfect companion to the star of the box - the carnitas. But what truly sets Carnitas Don Jose apart from the rest isn t just the quality of their food - it s the evident passion and care that goes into crafting each meal. This isn t fast food; this is a love letter to traditional Mexican cooking, delivered conveniently in a takeout box. Carnitas Don Jose is not just a pit-stop for food   its a destination for anyone who appreciates good, hearty meals that stay with you long after the last bite. My advice? Don t just pass by this gem. Stop, order, and prepare to be pleasantly surprised. After all, great food isn t just about satisfying hunger, its about the experience. And Carnitas Don Jose offers an experience you wont forget.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Dear David Thank you so much for taking the time to share your incredible experience at Carnitas Don Jose. We are thrilled to hear that your takeout lunch box, filled with our tantalizing tacos, left such a lasting impression on you. Once again, thank you for choosing Carnitas Don Jose. We look forward to serving you again soon and creating more unforgettable moments for you and all our valued customers. Best regards, The Carnitas Don Jose Team

Let me start by saying I am Mexican, like 100% newly arrived in Vancouver, my wife is a picky eater and not a huge fan of American food at least not for the long term. Its been a process to find authentic Mexican food because mostly its Tex-Mex or has some spices/flavors changed to accommodate the Canadian taste buds (this is not hate guys, we do have Mexican style of all foods to accommodate our taste). I am saying all of this just to tell you these are 100% authentic Mexican carnitas, source? My wifes family is from Michoacan, so we know what good carnitas are and these definitely made it to our list, we ordered from Doordash but well definitely visit the restaurant- you guys made our Friday morning much better. Muy buena comida muchachos les deseo lo mejor y seguire probando su comida!

reviews.review_text: For the first time we went to try Don Joses famous carnitas in Vancouver. When we arrived, we were greeted very well by a clean environment and the very friendly staff asked about the carnitas, which the person who charged us told us everything they had and what they were selling, I didnt know. Yes, it was Don Jose who offered us the test, which was very kind and we loved it without thinking. We ordered a kilo of carnitas, a liter of butter and an abanero sauce that he offered us. He asked us where we were from. We answered that we were from Jalisco and he told us. He said that from Michoacan now I understand why the carnitas are so delicious, the best ones are from Michoacan and even more so when you are in Vancouver and the tests you fall in love more than when you are dating...... Greetings from Francisco and Gabriela. ...on Sunday, May 28, 2023, I hope to go soon
